-- GP Investments Sells Its Stake in Baladare for $1, Lends Up to $23 Million
-- Laura Price
-- 2010-06-21T06:53:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-21/gp-investments-sells-its-stake-in-baladare-for-1-lends-up-to-23-million.html

          
          
             GP Investments Ltd ., a private-
equity company,  sold its stake  in Baladare Participacoes SA for
$1 and agreed to provide as much as 40 million reais ($23
million) of long-term financing to the company, which owns 78.9
percent of  Imbra SA .  
 GP Investments said it expects a negative accounting impact
of $60 million from the transaction, which will be reported on
its income statement.  
